{
    "text": "\ud83d\udd35Whitby Abbey\ud83d\udd35 \u26abThe 7th-century Christian monastery was situated on the East Cliff above Whitby in North Yorkshire, England. \u26abThe ruins of the abbey have been used by sailors as a landmark at the headland. \ud83e\udddb\u200d\u2642The famous author\" Bram Stoker \"got the inspiration for his epic novel \"Dracula\" from the colossal remains of Whitby Abbey. \ud83d\udc7bThere is also a legend about a pale ghost of a lady who wanders in the shadowy ruins of the monastery. \ud83d\ude28The legend says that the lady was bricked up alive in one of the walls and that she was frequently seen in one of the crumbled windows. \u26abSince the 20th century, the substantial ruins of the church have been declared a Grade I Listed building and are in the care of English Heritage;the site museum is housed in Cholmley House.  \ud83e\udddb\u200d\u2642 Follow me @ancient.scientist and check out many posts about our world's ancient history\ud83d\ude09  \ud83d\udce2For Business/ Promotion Dm me \ud83d\udce9  \ud83d\udcf8I don't own any of these Photos and i give all credit to the respective owners.  #tower #castle #abbey #whitby #whitbyabbey #abbey #england #uk #ghost #dracula #archaeology #history #ancient #art #world #traveling #discovery #ancienthistory #travel #archaeological #historic #london #paris #photography #usa #vacation #travelphotography #book",
